⛽ Fuel Tracker – Privacy Policy

Last updated: 9/12/2025

1. Introduction

Fuel Tracker (“the App”) allows users to record fuel usage, log meter readings, track tanks and machines, and monitor total consumption.

This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your information. By using the App, you agree to this policy.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 Account Information

If the App uses accounts, we may collect:

Email address

Password (securely stored by authentication provider such as Firebase, never visible to us)

If the App does not use accounts, you may skip this section.

2.2 Fuel Logging Data

We store data you manually enter, including:

Tank names and meter readings

Machine names

Fuel volumes added or removed

Total and reset counters

Timestamp of each fill or usage

This information is stored only to provide the App’s core functionality.

2.3 Device Information

The following non-personal information may be collected automatically:

Device model

Operating system

App version

Crash logs and performance data

This data helps improve app reliability.

2.4 Location Data (If enabled)

If you choose to attach a location to a fuel entry, the App may collect:

GPS coordinates at the time of logging
The App does not track or record your location continuously.

3. How We Use Your Information

We use collected information to:

Display fuel logs, readings, and machine/tank data

Calculate fuel usage and discrepancies

Improve app performance

Provide backup or sync features if cloud storage is enabled

We do not use your information for advertising.

4. Sharing of Information

We do not sell, share, or disclose your personal information except in the following situations:

4.1 Service Providers

If the App uses cloud services (e.g., Firebase), they may process data on our behalf to:

Store app data

Authenticate users

Provide analytics or crash reporting

4.2 Legal Requirements

We may disclose information if required by law or to protect the safety and rights of users.

5. Data Storage & Security

All stored data is protected using industry-standard encryption (HTTPS/TLS for data in transit).

If cloud storage is used, the provider (e.g., Firebase/Google Cloud) encrypts data at rest.

Passwords are securely hashed and never accessible to us.

We take reasonable measures to protect your information, but no method of electronic storage is completely secure.

6. Data Retention

We retain app data for as long as:

You maintain an account

Your data remains in the cloud database

You may request deletion of your account and associated data at any time by contacting support.

If the App stores data only on-device, deleting the app will remove all stored data.

7. Children’s Privacy

Fuel Tracker is not intended for children under 13.
We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

8. Your Rights

Depending on your region, you may have rights to:

Access your data

Correct or update your data

Request deletion of your data

Withdraw consent

To exercise these rights, contact support using the information below.

9. Changes to This Policy

We may update this policy from time to time.
Changes will be posted on this page with a new “Last Updated” date.

10. Contact Us

If you have any questions or need support, please contact:

Email: christianfrandsen6@hotmail.com

